						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of money to the temple (purpose not clear) by a native of Toṅgamaṅgalam in Tirunaṟaiyūr-nāḍu, who is said to have belonged to a regiment (?) called the Mūtta-Pirāntaka-Aṇukkar very probably after Parāntaka I.</p>						

